where N = L ϫ L is the size of the lattice, J is the coupling constant, and the sum over j runs over the nearest neighbors of a given site i ͓nn͑i͔͒. Here we implemented the Metropolis Monte Carlo algorithm ͓24,25͔ to solve the Ising model, which takes into account that the system is in contact with a

