heat bath at temperature T. The algorithm can be summa-
rized as follow: ͑1͒ Establish an initial conﬁguration ͑i.e., all spins ran-
dom͒. ͑2͒ Choose a spin at random and ﬂip it. ͑3͒ Compute the change in energy ⌬E = Etrial − Eold due to
the ﬂip. ͑4͒ If ⌬E Յ 0 accept the change and keep the new con-
ﬁguration of the lattice. ͑5͒ If ⌬E Ͼ 0 compute the transition probability w
= e−⌬E/kT. ͑6͒ Generate a random number r in the unit interval. ͑7͒ If r Յ w accept the change and keep the new conﬁgu-
